# Linux as a Building

Linux can be understood as an office building.

## Root (/)

The main entrance of the building.

Everything starts here.

## /home

Private offices for users.

Example:

/home/ubuntu

## /etc

The control room.

Contains configuration files that control system behaviour.

## /var

Storage room for changing data.

Examples:

- logs
- caches
- temporary application data

## /var/log

Security camera recordings of the building.

Stores system logs.

## /bin

Shared toolbox.

Contains common commands:

- ls
- cp
- mv
- cat

## Key Takeaway

Every directory has a purpose.

Understanding the purpose is more important than memorising paths
